A viral video of the National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Bola Tinubu’s wet agbada has gotten the attention of Nigerian activist, Omoyele Sowore.  According to Sowore, Tinubu is not well. In the viral clip, a security personnel was seen gazing at the wet part of the dress while closing his nostrils. Reacting to the video, Sowore urged the 2023 presidential aspirant to proceed for medical treatment, saying he is sick. According to the popular activist, if the former Lagos State Governor continues with his ambition, the presidency may be converted to a “hospice”. “Bola Tinubu is sick, he needs medical treatment NOT Nigeria’s presidential seat. The Presidency should not be converted to a hospice! #WeCantContinueLikeThis #RevolutionNow”, Sowore posted on his verified Facebook page.  Source There was drama at a protest venue today in Abuja after Nigerian activist and former presidential candidate, Omoyele Sowore was reportedly sent home by #EndSars protesters. His attempt to beg and explain was rebuffed by the #EndSARS protesters who didn't want to hear anything from him. According to reports, he… In "News" Nigerian activist, Omoyele Sowore has called out All Progressives Congress national leader, Bola Tinubu after he declared his intention to become President in 2023. Sowore, in a post on his Facebook page on Monday, said Tinubu might consult with whosoever he wanted but warned that this ambition might never be… In "News" By Ismaila Chafe Abuja - The Presidency has dismissed insinuations in the media about the re-arrest by the Department of State Services (DSS) of Omoyele Sowore, saying no government will allow anybody to openly call for destabilization in the country and do nothing. The President’s Senior Special Assistant on Media… In "News"